        h3.mb30 Who Must File an FBAR?
        p You must file an FBAR if you meet BOTH of the following criteria:
        ul.list
          li You are a U.S. taxpayer who has an ownership or signature authority over one or more foreign financial accounts
          li The total value of all offshore financial accounts exceed $10,000 at any time during the calendar year.

      .col-xs-6.content.right
        h3.mb30 Why should I disclose?
        p Failure to file an FBAR may result in one of the following three penalties:
        ul.list
          li Negligent violation: maximum of $500 per violation.
          li Non-willful violation: maximum of $10,000 perviolation.
          li Willful violation: the greater of $100,000 or 50% of the total balance of the foreign account per violation

        p.small * The taxpayer may also be subject to criminal prosecution.